# Supabase Local Development

## config.toml Format (CLI v2.75+)

Top-level `project_id`, NOT `[project]` section:

```toml
# ✅ GOOD (v2.75+)
project_id = "snacky-local"

# ❌ BAD (old format — causes "invalid keys: project" error)
[project]
id = "snacky-local"
```

## Google OAuth + React Native

`skip_nonce_check = true` is REQUIRED for `signInWithIdToken()` to work locally:

```toml
[auth.external.google]
enabled = true
client_id = "env(GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID)"
secret = "env(GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET)"
skip_nonce_check = true   # Required for native mobile sign-in
```

Without this, you get: "Passed nonce and nonce in id_token should either both exist or not."

## Extension Names

The pgvector extension is named `vector`, not `pgvector`:

```sql
-- ✅ GOOD
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "vector" WITH SCHEMA extensions;

-- ❌ BAD — "pgvector" is not available
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "pgvector" WITH SCHEMA extensions;
```

## pgvector Index Dimension Limits

pgvector 0.8.x limits HNSW and IVFFlat indexes to **2000 dimensions**. If your vectors exceed this (e.g., voyage-4-large = 2048), you cannot create a vector index. Use exact (sequential) scan instead and document the limitation.

## Seed Data + DB Triggers

If a trigger on `auth.users` INSERT auto-creates `public.users` rows, the seed file must NOT manually INSERT into `public.users` — it will hit a duplicate key error. Instead:

```sql
-- ✅ GOOD — let trigger create users, then UPDATE profiles
INSERT INTO auth.users (...) VALUES (...);  -- trigger fires → creates public.users + user_profiles
UPDATE user_profiles SET goal_type = 'maintain' WHERE user_id = '...';

-- ❌ BAD — conflicts with trigger
INSERT INTO auth.users (...) VALUES (...);   -- trigger creates public.users
INSERT INTO users (...) VALUES (...);         -- duplicate key error!
```

## Hermes + Supabase Realtime (React Native)

Hermes makes `URL.protocol` read-only. Supabase Realtime client crashes on construction trying to set `wsUrl.protocol`. Fix: import the URL polyfill as the FIRST import in `index.js`:

```js
// apps/mobile/index.js — MUST be first import
import 'react-native-url-polyfill/auto';
import './src/i18n';
// ...
```

## Colima Docker Compatibility

If using Colima instead of Docker Desktop, disable analytics to avoid Docker socket mount errors:

```toml
[analytics]
enabled = false
```
